Your Honor,

I stand before you today, humbled by the gravity of the offense I have committed. I, Aleksander Nowak, solemnly plead guilty to the assault charges brought against me.

Allow me to briefly explain the circumstances surrounding the incident. My employee had made a serious mistake at work, an error that would have significant financial implications for my company. Frustration and anger welled up inside me, clouding my judgment and leading me to act impulsively. In a moment of poor control, I pushed him to the ground and kicked him in the stomach.

Immediately after the incident, remorse consumed me. Recognizing the severity of my actions, I rushed my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I regret the distress I have caused him, and I sincerely apologize to both the victim and his family for the pain and fear they undoubtedly experienced.

In an attempt to rectify my wrongdoing, I have taken steps to provide support and aid to the victim. I have offered to pay for his remaining hospital bills, understanding the financial burden my actions may have placed on him. It is my genuine hope that this gesture can alleviate some of the stress he and his family are enduring.

Moreover, I am compelled to emphasize that, prior to this unfortunate incident, I have led a life free from criminal behavior. With no prior convictions, I stand before you as an individual who has always strived to uphold the law and contribute positively to society.

While I cannot change the past, I am committed to taking proactive measures to prevent such an offense from happening again. The shame I feel serves as an impetus for personal growth and self-reflection. I have enrolled in anger management courses to address the underlying issues that led to this violent outburst. This endeavor demonstrates my earnest desire to learn from this mistake and ensure it is not repeated.

Lastly, I would like to express the distress and turmoil I have endured as a consequence of my actions. The guilt and regret I carry with me every day serve as a constant reminder of the harm I have caused. This internal suffering, combined with the profound remorse I display, testifies to the genuine remorse I feel.

Your Honor, I stand before you today to plead guilty, recognizing the wrong I have done. I acknowledge the harm I have caused, and I am genuinely remorseful. I am deeply committed to making amends, both through financial compensation and personal growth. I ask for leniency and an opportunity to demonstrate that I can be a law-abiding and responsible citizen moving forward.

Thank you for your attention and consideration.

Sincerely,
Aleksander Nowak

