1453
Your Honor, 

I, Aleksander Nowak, stand before you today with deep remorse for the assault charges brought against me. I humbly and unequivocally plead guilty to the offense, fully acknowledging the gravity of my actions.

Allow me to provide an explanation for the circumstances surrounding the regrettable incident. My employee's serious mistake at work weighed heavily on me, as it posed significant financial consequences for my company. Overwhelmed by a surge of anger and frustration, I reacted impulsively by pushing him to the ground and delivering a kick to his stomach.

Immediately after the assault, a profound realization of the severity of my actions washed over me. Recognizing the harm I had caused, I swiftly rushed my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure he received prompt medical attention. To the victim and his family, I extend my deepest apologies for the pain and distress I have inflicted upon them.

I wholeheartedly accept complete responsibility for my behavior and the resulting consequences. In the spirit of true remorse, I offer my guilty plea not only as an admission of my wrongdoing, but also as a genuine recognition of the severity of the offense. I understand that my guilty plea serves as a mitigating factor, a step towards accountability and a testament to my willingness to take responsibility for my actions.

